WEBVTT

00:02.377 --> 00:05.756
GREAT DRAGON:
In a land of myth and a time of magic...

00:05.923 --> 00:10.802
...the destiny of a great kingdom
rests on the shoulders of a young man.

00:10.969 --> 00:13.847
His name: Merlin.

00:20.521 --> 00:21.813
[CROWD CHEERING AND LAUGHING]

00:27.903 --> 00:30.864
Oh! Did you see that?

00:32.824 --> 00:35.536
It's a man throwing sticks in the air.

00:36.453 --> 00:40.582
What's wrong? It's your birthday.
A huge feast is being held in your honor.

00:40.791 --> 00:43.544
You've got dancers, jugglers
and acrobats to entertain you.

00:43.710 --> 00:45.712
[SIGHS]

00:47.005 --> 00:48.840
It must be a terrible burden.

00:49.007 --> 00:51.301
Perhaps I'm less easily impressed
than you.

00:51.468 --> 00:55.472
-I'm really looking forward to it.
-Because you have the mind of a child.

00:55.639 --> 00:57.641
[QUIETLY]
And yet I'm still more intelligent than you.

00:57.808 --> 01:00.018
ARTHUR:
| heard that.

01:07.067 --> 01:09.069
You have misplaced something, Geldred?

01:10.070 --> 01:13.657
Our special gift to the prince.
| cannot find it anywhere.

01:14.616 --> 01:20.247
Geldred, I took the liberty of
ensuring their safe passage myself.

01:24.209 --> 01:26.962
We must make sure that
this is a celebration...

01:27.129 --> 01:29.965
...the young prince will never forget.

02:03.957 --> 02:06.418
ARTHUR: The court discussed
the annual levy this morning.

02:06.627 --> 02:10.213
The council suggested we raise it, but
| feel the people are already overburdened.

02:10.380 --> 02:14.343
We should not talk about
matters of court today.

02:15.135 --> 02:16.178
Father?

02:16.345 --> 02:20.891
You think I would ever forget
that today is the anniversary...

02:21.058 --> 02:22.851
...of your birth?

02:26.647 --> 02:29.149
| take it there are plans for...

02:29.316 --> 02:33.195
...Suitable celebrations this evening.

02:33.362 --> 02:36.531
A feast and, um...

02:36.698 --> 02:38.700
...some entertainment.

02:38.867 --> 02:42.120
-I'll tell you about it tomorrow.
-Nonsense.

02:43.413 --> 02:47.125
You think I would miss
my son's anniversary?

02:54.424 --> 02:56.426
[CROWD GASPING AND LAUGHING]

02:56.718 --> 02:57.969
[BAND PLAYING UPBEAT MUSIC]

03:03.809 --> 03:05.936
[CROWD APPLAUDING]

03:08.522 --> 03:10.524
| require a volunteer.

03:11.149 --> 03:14.111
Prince Arthur, what better
or more fitting occasion...

03:14.277 --> 03:17.030
...for you to demonstrate
your legendary bravery?

03:17.197 --> 03:19.825
Do you accept the challenge?

03:22.869 --> 03:23.995
Of course.

03:24.162 --> 03:26.164
[CROWD APPLAUDING]

03:26.915 --> 03:28.125
[CHUCKLES]

03:30.419 --> 03:32.421
MERLIN: Is this safe?
-It's knife throwing, Merlin.

03:32.587 --> 03:35.173
Of course it's not safe.
| could hardly refuse his challenge.

03:51.898 --> 03:54.359
Do not fear, my lord.
| never miss my target.

03:54.526 --> 03:56.903
Good. Glad to hear it.

03:57.070 --> 03:59.573
-May 17?
-Uh-- Unh.

04:18.132 --> 04:20.552
[CROWD CHEERING AND APPLAUDING]

04:28.185 --> 04:30.187
[CROWD CHEERING AND APPLAUDING]

04:53.585 --> 04:55.587
[BLADE PLUNGES]
[CROWD GASPS]

05:00.008 --> 05:02.010
[CROWD CHEERING AND APPLAUDING]

05:02.427 --> 05:04.429
[BAND PLAYING UPBEAT MUSIC]

05:21.530 --> 05:24.533
See, Merlin? Nothing to worry about.

05:27.035 --> 05:30.872
In a few hours time, the sedative
on the apple will begin to take effect.

05:31.039 --> 05:33.041
The prince will be defenseless.

05:33.208 --> 05:35.794
Then we will strike.

05:39.589 --> 05:41.716
[CROWD CHEERING AND APPLAUDING]

05:42.384 --> 05:45.512
You're telling me you weren't
even a little bit scared?

05:45.679 --> 05:48.306
Of course I wasn't. I'm a warrior.

05:48.473 --> 05:51.977
You learn to control your fear,
to channel it.

05:54.312 --> 05:56.565
You looked scared.

05:57.399 --> 06:00.569
It was good to see my father
enjoying himself.

06:00.986 --> 06:03.655
He looked a little quiet
towards the end there.

06:03.822 --> 06:06.283
-Perhaps I should go see him.
-Are you sure that's a good idea?

06:06.449 --> 06:08.785
-You can barely stand up.
-Are you saying I'm drunk?

06:08.952 --> 06:11.955
No. I'm just saying I don't think you
should be wandering around the palace.

06:12.122 --> 06:13.790
And why is that?

06:13.957 --> 06:15.625
You're not wearing any trousers.

06:17.752 --> 06:19.796
Good point.

07:15.310 --> 07:16.603
ARTHUR:
Guards!

07:17.520 --> 07:18.605
Guards!

07:26.446 --> 07:29.074
Goodbye, Arthur Pendragon.

07:30.325 --> 07:33.578
It'll take more than a coward like you
to kill my son.

07:37.290 --> 07:39.292
[BOTH GRUNTING]

08:04.943 --> 08:06.945
[GROANS]

08:07.988 --> 08:10.865
Have you anything to say
to your son before I kill him?

08:39.727 --> 08:42.355
UTHER: Unh.
ARTHUR: Father?

08:52.407 --> 08:53.908
No.

08:54.075 --> 08:56.119
Guards.

08:56.661 --> 08:59.497
-I'll go get help.
-Stay with me.

08:59.664 --> 09:01.291
I'm here, Father.

09:04.627 --> 09:06.588
Guards!

09:06.755 --> 09:08.256
Someone!

09:08.923 --> 09:10.675
We need help.

09:10.884 --> 09:13.053
-It's my time.
-No.

09:13.219 --> 09:15.180
You can't die.

09:15.513 --> 09:19.392
| know you will make me proud,
as you always have.

09:19.559 --> 09:23.104
-You will be a great king.
-I'm not ready.

09:23.271 --> 09:26.191
You-- You have been ready
for some time, Arthur.

09:26.357 --> 09:27.484
No.

09:27.650 --> 09:32.197
- I need you.
- I know I've not been a good father.

09:32.363 --> 09:34.240
I've put my duty to Camelot first.

09:34.407 --> 09:35.909
-No.
-I'm sorry.

09:36.076 --> 09:37.410
Don't say that.

09:38.703 --> 09:42.582
But know this, Arthur.

09:43.208 --> 09:45.668
I've always loved you.

10:07.357 --> 10:09.150
ARTHUR:
Gaius.

10:10.068 --> 10:12.070
Can you treat him?

10:12.237 --> 10:16.241
The blade has touched his heart.
He's bleeding inside.

10:16.407 --> 10:19.369
There must be something--
There must be something you can do.

10:19.536 --> 10:21.121
Please, Gaius.

10:21.287 --> 10:24.749
It's only a matter of time, I'm afraid.

10:25.208 --> 10:27.544
I'm sorry, Arthur.

10:36.261 --> 10:38.596
AGRAVAINE: We traced the assassin
to the town of Wenham.

10:38.763 --> 10:40.932
It's in Odin's land.
It seems he hired him...

10:41.099 --> 10:43.685
...to kill you to avenge
the death of his son.

10:44.727 --> 10:46.855
Camelot's thoughts
are with you, Arthur.

10:47.021 --> 10:49.732
But if there's anything I can do...

10:50.567 --> 10:53.319
Your support means a great deal to me.
Thank you.

11:06.624 --> 11:08.835
-What news of my father?
-There is no change.

11:10.879 --> 11:13.006
Why isn't Gaius doing something then?

11:13.173 --> 11:15.800
Because there is nothing he can do.

11:34.485 --> 11:36.738
Now, is that any way
to greet an old friend?

11:38.114 --> 11:40.450
-I wasn't expecting you today.
- I had to see you.

11:40.617 --> 11:42.952
| bring good news.

11:43.119 --> 11:44.662
Better than we could have hoped for.

11:45.914 --> 11:47.415
What is it?

11:47.582 --> 11:50.668
Uther has been mortally wounded.

11:51.169 --> 11:55.215
He's on his deathbed. Gaius says
he only has a few days to live.

11:56.716 --> 11:59.344
| hope the image of my face
haunts him.

12:02.180 --> 12:04.557
-How is Arthur?
-Devastated.

12:04.766 --> 12:06.726
Poor boy can't think straight.

12:07.518 --> 12:10.021
Then we must strike
while he's vulnerable.

12:10.188 --> 12:11.898
When Uther dies,
the kingdom will be weak.

12:15.443 --> 12:19.572
We must choose
our moments carefully.

12:21.991 --> 12:24.535
Who knows what opportunities
the coming weeks will hold?

12:40.385 --> 12:41.552
| appreciate your kindness...

12:43.429 --> 12:45.056
...everything you're doing for him.

12:46.599 --> 12:48.142
| do it for you.

12:52.647 --> 12:54.315
Oh, Arthur.

12:55.066 --> 12:56.693
| can't watch him die.

13:01.447 --> 13:05.451
There's still so much I want to say to him.

13:11.165 --> 13:13.418
He cannot die.

13:26.681 --> 13:28.683
[DOOR OPENS]

13:38.151 --> 13:40.236
What's going on?

13:40.778 --> 13:43.239
It's a vigil for your father.

13:43.406 --> 13:46.242
The people wish to share their grief.

13:46.409 --> 13:50.038
Why are they behaving like he's already
dead when there's still life in his body?

13:51.414 --> 13:54.000
MERLIN:
They're preparing themselves for the worst.

13:57.003 --> 13:59.088
Well, they can give up hope, but I won't.

13:59.255 --> 14:00.798
| know.

14:03.926 --> 14:07.638
It's hard to accept.
| wish it wasn't so, but...

14:12.935 --> 14:15.938
...there really is nothing
that can be done.

14:20.360 --> 14:22.904
There is a way to heal my father.

14:25.198 --> 14:26.574
How?

14:29.952 --> 14:31.579
With magic.

14:35.708 --> 14:38.378
-Arthur's planning on using magic?
MERLIN: He's desperate.

14:38.544 --> 14:41.464
He knows it's his only hope
of healing Uther.

14:41.631 --> 14:44.717
Merlin, please tell me
you're not going to do this.

14:44.884 --> 14:46.761
I'd be lying if I said no.

14:46.928 --> 14:50.473
You can't risk exposing yourself like this.
It's too dangerous.

14:50.640 --> 14:53.810
Arthur didn't recognize me last time
when I was 80 years old.

14:53.976 --> 14:56.604
-There's no reason why he should this time.
-The last time...

14:56.771 --> 15:00.024
...you used an aging spell, you nearly
had yourself burnt at the stake.

15:00.191 --> 15:03.111
-It's worth the risk.
-Do you think Uther is going to thank you...

15:03.277 --> 15:04.987
...for healing him with magic?

15:05.154 --> 15:06.572
He's more likely to have you hanged.

15:06.739 --> 15:09.242
Uther will never change his attitude
towards magic. I know that.

15:09.409 --> 15:12.370
But if Arthur allows it
to be used to heal his father...

15:12.537 --> 15:14.789
...his attitude would be changed forever.

15:14.956 --> 15:16.833
He'll see that magic
can be a force for good.

15:18.042 --> 15:22.296
You of all people should know that the use
of powerful magic is fraught with danger.

15:22.463 --> 15:25.716
-If it works, I won't have to hide anymore.
-And if it doesn't?

15:26.259 --> 15:28.302
| can't stand by and watch you
do this, Merlin.

15:28.469 --> 15:31.139
Well, don't try and stop me, because...

15:32.098 --> 15:33.391
...you can't.

15:38.729 --> 15:41.190
You're playing
a dangerous game, Merlin.

15:43.067 --> 15:44.819
I've been playing a dangerous game...

15:44.986 --> 15:48.114
...since the first time
| set foot in Camelot.

15:49.532 --> 15:51.701
Maybe this is my chance
to change that.

15:55.163 --> 15:57.039
[SIGHS]

16:00.751 --> 16:03.713
Well? What did Gaius say?
Did he have any information?

16:03.880 --> 16:07.091
He didn't know much, but he has
heard of a sorcerer, an old man.

16:07.258 --> 16:09.218
He lives in the forest of Glaestig.

16:09.385 --> 16:11.179
Gaius thinks
he may be able to help you.

16:12.263 --> 16:15.391
-Will he lead me to him?
-He has told me all that he knows.

16:15.558 --> 16:17.602
We will have to find him ourselves.

16:20.021 --> 16:21.189
If you were me...

16:22.273 --> 16:25.318
...and it was your father...

16:26.068 --> 16:28.738
...would you use magic
to save his life?

16:32.283 --> 16:34.660
Yes, I would.
| would do whatever it took.

16:44.795 --> 16:46.255
Prepare the horses.

16:47.215 --> 16:48.758
Gather supplies.

16:49.008 --> 16:50.718
We ride at first light.

17:07.108 --> 17:08.694
[DOOR OPENS]

17:08.861 --> 17:12.073
Arthur. What news
of your father's health?

17:13.406 --> 17:15.409
No improvement, I'm afraid.

17:16.117 --> 17:17.161
Something's on your mind.

17:20.540 --> 17:22.375
| didn't want to go behind your back.

17:25.627 --> 17:28.881
| have decided to use magic
to heal my father.

17:29.757 --> 17:32.009
| would strongly advise
against such a course of action.

17:32.176 --> 17:36.138
-There is no other way.
-Magic caused your mother's death, Arthur.

17:36.347 --> 17:39.725
-If you respect her memory, you cannot.
-Would you see my father die?

17:39.934 --> 17:41.936
[SIGHS]

17:43.062 --> 17:44.564
Perhaps it is his time.

17:47.024 --> 17:49.986
Look, I know we've both suffered
because of magic...

17:50.152 --> 17:53.823
...but I can't stand by
and let my father die.

17:53.990 --> 17:55.408
My mind's made up.

18:13.384 --> 18:16.679
Are you sure this is the right place?
It looks like a charcoal maker's hut.

18:16.846 --> 18:19.807
The old man can hardly make
a living practicing magic.

18:19.974 --> 18:24.395
| think that a lot of sorcerers
are in the charcoal business.

18:35.448 --> 18:37.825
Are you joining me?

18:40.161 --> 18:41.537
We don't want to overwhelm him.

18:42.622 --> 18:46.667
Probably doesn't get many visitors.
I'll stay out here and watch the horses.

18:46.834 --> 18:50.254
| have never met anyone
who's so scared so often.

18:50.463 --> 18:53.424
Scream like a big girl
if there's any trouble.

18:53.591 --> 18:55.551
Don't worry. You'll hear me.

18:55.718 --> 18:56.927
[KNOCKS]

19:06.020 --> 19:07.938
Hello?

19:14.945 --> 19:18.240
There's no one here.
Are you sure this is the right place?

19:18.449 --> 19:21.118
I'm absolutely certain of it.
I'm sure he'll be back soon.

19:21.285 --> 19:22.495
How do you know?

19:22.662 --> 19:26.499
He's a doddery old man. He can't have gone
far. If you want his help, you'll have to just...

19:26.666 --> 19:28.959
...wait for him inside.

19:29.126 --> 19:30.503
Where are you sneaking off to?

19:31.921 --> 19:33.756
| have to pee.

19:34.674 --> 19:36.759
So unless you want
to come and watch me--

19:36.967 --> 19:38.552
You should wait for him inside.

19:38.719 --> 19:41.180
Why would I want to watch you?

19:41.347 --> 19:42.932
There's the hut. I have to--

19:44.517 --> 19:45.976
Make yourself at home.

19:56.278 --> 19:58.280
[SIGHS]

19:59.949 --> 20:01.951
[SPEAKING IN ANCIENT LANGUAGE]

20:18.300 --> 20:19.927
[DOOR OPENS]

20:25.391 --> 20:26.434
[SCOFFS]

20:26.600 --> 20:27.727
You.

20:28.811 --> 20:32.648
So we meet again, Arthur Pendragon.

20:34.817 --> 20:37.069
You have come to kill me?

20:37.278 --> 20:38.779
No, that wasn't my intention.

20:41.782 --> 20:43.367
[CROCKERY CLATTERS]

20:47.329 --> 20:48.789
| broke a pot.

20:48.956 --> 20:49.957
[SCOFFS]

20:50.124 --> 20:53.377
You always were a clumsy fool.

20:53.544 --> 20:54.628
Excuse me?

20:55.671 --> 20:57.423
[CHUCKLES]

20:59.133 --> 21:04.346
So if you haven't come all this way
to kill me, why have you come here?

21:04.513 --> 21:08.225
| take it you didn't come all this way
just to smash my favorite pot.

21:08.684 --> 21:10.853
If I'd known who you were,
| wouldn't have come at all.

21:12.104 --> 21:16.275
| thought you may have come to ask me
to use magic to heal your father.

21:22.948 --> 21:25.159
How did you know?

21:25.326 --> 21:29.205
| know more than you
can possibly comprehend.

21:29.413 --> 21:32.374
Well, given your hatred for my father
and everything he stands for...

21:32.541 --> 21:34.710
...I've clearly had a wasted journey.

21:34.877 --> 21:37.838
Do not suppose that you know my mind.

21:42.843 --> 21:43.928
Will you help me?

21:46.096 --> 21:48.641
You are asking me...

21:48.808 --> 21:52.186
...to save the life of a man
that would have me executed?

21:52.353 --> 21:55.356
| know what I'm asking of you, and
| know you have no reason to help me...

21:55.523 --> 21:57.399
...but you're my father's only hope.

21:57.566 --> 22:00.361
I'll give you anything you ask for:
land, gold.

22:00.528 --> 22:03.656
-Name your price.
- I do not want your gold!

22:04.615 --> 22:06.867
All I have ever wanted...

22:07.034 --> 22:09.578
...Is that people like me can live in peace.

22:09.745 --> 22:11.455
That those who practice magic...

22:11.622 --> 22:14.041
...are accepted rather than hunted.

22:16.877 --> 22:19.129
That is all I ask.

22:20.381 --> 22:22.174
That is the price...

22:23.133 --> 22:25.302
...of your father's life.

22:32.560 --> 22:34.979
| give you my solemn word.

22:35.145 --> 22:38.232
When I am king, things will be different.

22:38.691 --> 22:40.276
You won't have to live in fear.

22:43.737 --> 22:45.698
Then...

22:45.865 --> 22:48.784
...will help you.

22:49.201 --> 22:51.412
[CHUCKLING]

22:53.998 --> 22:56.709
Then there's no time to waste.
We must ride for Camelot immediately.

22:56.876 --> 22:59.169
-Now?
-My father weakens by the hour.

22:59.336 --> 23:02.339
But I have no horse.

23:02.506 --> 23:04.300
You can use Merlin's.
He'll have to walk back.

23:04.466 --> 23:08.220
You would make your servant
walk back to Camelot?

23:08.387 --> 23:10.806
| have a good mind not to help you.

23:10.973 --> 23:13.934
| don't care whose horse you use.

23:14.101 --> 23:16.312
We have to get back to Camelot
before it's too late.

23:17.021 --> 23:19.857
First, I must gather some rare herbs.

23:20.024 --> 23:22.484
They are an essential part of the cure.

23:22.651 --> 23:27.865
| will come to Camelot at nightfall. If you
want my help, that is how it needs to be.

23:29.241 --> 23:34.038
| will meet you at the lower gate
outside the town.

23:34.204 --> 23:36.832
Give me your word you'll be there.

23:37.875 --> 23:39.543
You have my word.

23:42.254 --> 23:44.006
Now just wait here one moment!

23:45.215 --> 23:46.759
Why?

23:46.926 --> 23:50.054
Questions. So many questions.

23:50.262 --> 23:55.142
For once in your life, would you
just do what you're told?

23:56.852 --> 23:58.854
[DOOR OPENS THEN CLOSES]

23:59.855 --> 24:01.732
All right.

24:21.293 --> 24:22.461
[BURPS]

24:31.345 --> 24:33.347
Merlin?

24:34.014 --> 24:36.767
[BRUSH RUSTLING]

24:45.943 --> 24:47.569
[SIGHS]

24:48.779 --> 24:50.739
What were you doing?

24:50.906 --> 24:52.574
Peeing.

24:52.741 --> 24:55.077
You mean to say you were peeing
all the time I was in there?

24:55.244 --> 24:58.455
-Yeah. I really had to go.
-There is definitely something...

24:58.622 --> 24:59.873
...very wrong with you.

25:07.881 --> 25:11.760
Merlin! I was worried.
| thought something had happened.

25:11.927 --> 25:16.098
Well, apart from Arthur thinking there's
something very wrong with my bladder...

25:16.265 --> 25:17.683
...everything went to plan.

25:17.850 --> 25:20.644
| take it that this means
you're going through with it.

25:20.811 --> 25:23.772
If I can heal Uther,
Arthur has given me his word...

25:23.939 --> 25:27.276
...that when he's king, magic will no longer
be outlawed. This could change everything.

25:27.443 --> 25:30.487
What if something goes wrong?
What of Arthur's attitude to magic then?

25:30.654 --> 25:34.074
| live with the risk of being exposed
every day. If I don't take this opportunity...

25:34.241 --> 25:37.036
...maybe I'll spend the rest of my life
having to hide who I really am.

25:37.202 --> 25:40.664
Everyone's always telling me I have this
great destiny. Maybe this is it. I have to try.

25:49.048 --> 25:51.425
Arthur has gone to consult
with a sorcerer.

25:51.592 --> 25:54.803
He intends to use magic to heal Uther.

25:54.970 --> 25:57.806
Then we must see to it that he fails.

25:59.266 --> 26:02.352
[SPEAKING IN ANCIENT LANGUAGE]

26:24.708 --> 26:28.420
-It's cold.
- I have bound it to the left-hand path.

26:30.380 --> 26:33.884
-Place the charm around Uther's neck.
-What will it do to him?

26:34.718 --> 26:38.388
The force of any healing magic
will be reversed and magnified tenfold.

26:40.516 --> 26:43.894
By trying to cure his father,
Arthur will seal his fate.

26:45.646 --> 26:47.314
Arthur will never forgive himself.

26:48.315 --> 26:49.900
He'll be destroyed.

26:50.067 --> 26:53.112
And a broken prince
will make a terrible king.

26:58.617 --> 27:01.537
| promised Arthur I could heal Uther.
| can't even find the right spell.

27:01.703 --> 27:04.581
That's because you're reading
the wrong books. Here.

27:04.748 --> 27:08.293
Gwillem of Cambria was as mad as a coot,
but there was never a better healer.

27:08.460 --> 27:10.462
Gaius, thank you.

27:18.637 --> 27:19.972
[GASPS]

27:21.890 --> 27:25.561
It was cold today.
Perhaps it's a good idea to start a fire.

27:26.145 --> 27:27.604
Of course.

27:45.497 --> 27:49.459
Finally, you will get
all that you deserve...

27:49.626 --> 27:51.920
...old friend.

27:57.467 --> 27:59.386
You must use only four drops.

27:59.553 --> 28:01.138
Any more could be dangerous.

28:01.305 --> 28:04.766
- I just hope I can remember the spell.
-You must trust your abilities, Merlin.

28:04.933 --> 28:07.811
ARTHUR: Merlin!
-You have to get rid of him.

28:07.978 --> 28:09.688
ARTHUR:
Merlin!

28:13.567 --> 28:15.110
GAIUS: Arthur.
-Gaius, have you seen...

28:15.277 --> 28:16.570
...my useless toad of a servant?

28:17.988 --> 28:20.240
-I'm afraid not.
-Well, where on earth is he?

28:21.408 --> 28:24.328
-Have you tried the tavern?
-The tavern. Of course.

28:25.245 --> 28:29.082
| am going to make him
wish he was never born.

28:30.334 --> 28:32.461
Why'd you tell him
| was in the tavern?

28:32.628 --> 28:34.504
It was the first thing
that popped into my head.

28:34.671 --> 28:37.382
Next time, go for the second or third thing
that pops into your head.

28:37.549 --> 28:39.551
Anywhere but the tavern.

28:44.598 --> 28:45.933
Good luck, Merlin.

28:55.859 --> 28:59.613
-I'd started to think you weren't coming.
- Igave you my word.

28:59.780 --> 29:01.573
And here I am.

29:01.740 --> 29:03.492
Good. We must hurry.

29:03.659 --> 29:04.785
Hey!

29:04.952 --> 29:09.623
| am led to believe that
the king's palace is that way.

29:09.790 --> 29:12.626
| can hardly be seen walking through
the main gate with a known sorcerer.

29:12.793 --> 29:15.462
So you are already
going back on your word.

29:15.629 --> 29:18.340
You promised that I would no longer
have to live in fear.

29:18.507 --> 29:20.634
You're forgetting that you have yet
to heal my father.

29:20.801 --> 29:23.637
When you have, I'll give you
everything I promised.

29:39.611 --> 29:41.697
Is this really as fast
as you can walk?

29:41.863 --> 29:46.451
When you are as old as |,
we will see how fast you can walk.

29:46.618 --> 29:50.038
-I need to rest a moment.
-There's no time.

29:50.205 --> 29:53.250
Then perhaps you should carry me.

29:55.168 --> 29:59.506
Fine. If it means we get there
quicker, I will carry you.

29:59.673 --> 30:00.716
Come on.

30:00.882 --> 30:02.884
[SORCERER GRUNTING]

30:09.808 --> 30:11.310
Did you just kick me?

30:11.476 --> 30:15.856
Now who's wasting time?
Hyah! Unh!

30:16.023 --> 30:17.899
Hyah!

30:18.650 --> 30:21.987
Faster. Faster.

30:26.325 --> 30:27.617
You're dismissed.

30:27.784 --> 30:29.870
But, sire, we were instructed
not to leave our post.

30:30.037 --> 30:33.582
-And I said you're dismissed.
-Yes, my lord.

30:37.419 --> 30:39.421
[CLEARS THROAT]

31:11.578 --> 31:13.205
[INHALES SHARPLY]

31:13.580 --> 31:15.248
Wait.

31:15.999 --> 31:17.876
Is something wrong?

31:18.043 --> 31:21.338
My father has taught me never to trust
magic. Now I'm using it to save him.

31:21.505 --> 31:25.884
Your own life has been saved using magic
more times than you can possibly imagine.

31:27.010 --> 31:28.637
What on earth are you talking about?

31:28.804 --> 31:32.849
| merely mean to say
that magic is all around you.

31:33.016 --> 31:37.187
It is woven into
the very fabric of the world.

31:38.522 --> 31:41.733
How can I be sure
it's the right thing to do?

31:42.526 --> 31:47.656
| know you have suffered
because of magic...

31:49.449 --> 31:51.785
...as many have.

31:52.577 --> 31:56.998
But not all magic and not all sorcerers...

31:57.165 --> 31:58.583
...are the same.

31:59.418 --> 32:04.506
| wish only to show you
that magic can be used for good.

32:04.673 --> 32:07.008
| hope...

32:07.175 --> 32:10.137
...one day you will see me
in a different light.

32:33.493 --> 32:35.495
[SPEAKING IN ANCIENT LANGUAGE]

33:17.287 --> 33:19.247
[GASPS]

33:21.333 --> 33:23.210
ARTHUR:
Father.

33:24.085 --> 33:25.921
Father.

33:26.546 --> 33:28.507
[SIGHS]

33:28.673 --> 33:30.550
Arthur.

33:30.717 --> 33:32.719
[CHUCKLING]

33:39.851 --> 33:40.977
[GROANING]

33:44.606 --> 33:46.233
-What's happening?
- I don't know.

33:47.776 --> 33:49.444
Well, do something.

33:54.449 --> 33:56.117
[EXHALES]

34:08.547 --> 34:09.880
He's dead.

34:10.715 --> 34:13.342
No. He can't be.

34:13.510 --> 34:15.303
Father.

34:16.888 --> 34:18.806
Father!

34:28.483 --> 34:30.443
What have you done?

34:32.487 --> 34:33.822
This was not supposed to happen.

34:33.989 --> 34:37.617
You gave me your word.
You-- You have killed him.

34:38.784 --> 34:40.203
-You killed him!
-No!

34:40.370 --> 34:41.788
You'll die for what you've done!

34:41.955 --> 34:43.956
[SHOUTS IN ANCIENT LANGUAGE]

34:48.837 --> 34:50.839
[BELL TOLLING]

35:18.950 --> 35:21.161
GAIUS:
I'm sorry, Arthur.

35:28.376 --> 35:30.378
The king is dead.

35:58.948 --> 36:01.493
The spell was working.

36:03.787 --> 36:06.122
I'm sure of it.

36:09.209 --> 36:11.878
I'd done everything right.
| don't know what happened.

36:12.712 --> 36:15.173
| think I do.

36:16.508 --> 36:19.010
| found it around Uther's neck.

36:19.177 --> 36:21.805
It's been enchanted.

36:21.971 --> 36:26.059
And such an enchantment would reverse
the effects of your healing spell.

36:26.226 --> 36:28.895
Uther didn't stand a chance.

36:30.271 --> 36:32.482
Morgana.

36:32.649 --> 36:33.775
| believe so.

36:43.159 --> 36:45.161
[DOOR OPENS]

36:48.998 --> 36:50.667
Uther's dead, isn't he?

36:51.960 --> 36:53.086
How did you know?

36:57.966 --> 37:02.721
| felt it, felt his pain.

37:03.763 --> 37:07.183
| thought Uther's death
would be cause for celebration.

37:07.350 --> 37:09.811
Arthur will replace him.

37:10.520 --> 37:13.857
There'll be no celebration
until I take my place upon the throne.

37:14.023 --> 37:16.484
That may be sooner than you think.

37:16.943 --> 37:20.739
Arthur is young, untested.

37:20.905 --> 37:26.536
He will look to his trusted uncle for
counsel, and I will ensure that he fails.

37:47.849 --> 37:49.350
| am so sorry.

37:53.813 --> 37:58.193
| should-- I sh--

37:59.110 --> 38:01.279
| wish that there was something
| could have done.

38:04.824 --> 38:06.743
Merlin, no one but me
is to blame for this.

38:06.910 --> 38:10.538
You are not to blame.
This isn't your fault.

38:11.372 --> 38:13.917
I'm entirely to blame.

38:16.961 --> 38:20.590
My father spent 20 years fighting magic.

38:22.634 --> 38:25.303
To think I knew better.

38:26.429 --> 38:30.683
| was so arrogant.

38:33.645 --> 38:35.647
That arrogance cost my father his life.

38:35.814 --> 38:39.776
You were only doing what you thought
was right. That old sorcerer meant no harm.

38:39.943 --> 38:41.694
Perhaps the spell went wrong.

38:41.861 --> 38:45.156
Uther was dying.

38:45.323 --> 38:47.158
Maybe nothing could have saved him.

38:48.493 --> 38:50.703
We'll never know.

38:53.289 --> 38:57.627
All I know for sure is that
I've lost both my parents to magic.

38:57.794 --> 39:01.005
It is pure evil.

39:02.423 --> 39:04.217
I'll never lose sight of that again.

39:07.053 --> 39:08.763
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

39:14.102 --> 39:16.104
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

40:08.865 --> 40:11.367
We must leave him to mourn.

40:14.829 --> 40:16.414
Merlin?

40:18.166 --> 40:20.752
This is all my fault.

40:20.919 --> 40:22.420
| killed him.

40:24.297 --> 40:28.134
You did not kill Uther. Morgana did.

40:29.469 --> 40:32.639
Uther's spirit died
when she broke his heart.

40:34.432 --> 40:36.476
We must look to the future.

40:38.978 --> 40:43.608
Uther's death will allow
Arthur's progression to the throne.

40:44.943 --> 40:48.071
We must hope it brings
peace and stability to the land.

40:49.072 --> 40:51.866
Magic will still be outlawed.

40:54.994 --> 40:56.913
| have turned Arthur against it forever.

40:59.874 --> 41:02.251
He'll never know who I really am.

41:02.418 --> 41:04.754
That time will come. I'm sure of it.

41:07.131 --> 41:11.511
Arthur will be under even more pressure
now that he is king.

41:12.387 --> 41:15.264
He will need you more than ever.

41:18.476 --> 41:20.561
There's nothing more to be done.

41:20.728 --> 41:22.355
Let's go and have some supper.

41:26.985 --> 41:28.403
| think I'll wait here.

42:28.588 --> 42:30.298
ARTHUR:
Merlin.

42:34.052 --> 42:36.387
It's a new day.

42:43.978 --> 42:45.271
Have you been here all night?

42:46.105 --> 42:47.940
| didn't want you to feel
that you were alone.

42:51.319 --> 42:53.404
You are a loyal friend, Merlin.

43:08.127 --> 43:09.796
[SHARPLY INHALES]

43:11.214 --> 43:12.340
You must be hungry.

43:14.634 --> 43:16.427
Starving.

43:16.594 --> 43:19.806
Me too. Come on.

43:21.182 --> 43:23.559
You can make us some breakfast.

43:34.445 --> 43:36.072
[PLAYING FANFARE]

43:51.879 --> 43:54.841
Will you solemnly promise and swear...

43:55.007 --> 43:56.884
...to govern the peoples of Camelot...

43:57.051 --> 44:01.222
...according to their respective
laws and customs?

44:01.389 --> 44:03.683
| solemnly swear so to do.

44:03.850 --> 44:06.060
MAN:
Will you, to your power...

44:06.227 --> 44:08.563
...cause law and justice, in mercy...

44:08.729 --> 44:12.608
...to be executed in all your judgments?

44:12.775 --> 44:14.819
| will.

44:16.779 --> 44:19.490
Then by the sacred law vested in me...

44:19.657 --> 44:24.537
...I crown you, Arthur, King of Camelot.

44:27.748 --> 44:29.667
Long live the king!

44:29.834 --> 44:31.878
ALL:
Long live the king!

44:32.044 --> 44:36.299
Long live the king!
Long live the king!

44:36.465 --> 44:40.136
Long live the king!
Long live the king!

44:40.303 --> 44:44.390
Long live the king!
Long live the king!

44:44.557 --> 44:47.310
Long live the king!

44:48.186 --> 44:49.979
GREAT DRAGON:
Merlin.

44:50.146 --> 44:52.190
GAIUS:
Borden is not a man to be trusted.

44:53.649 --> 44:55.610
-What do you want?
-To help you.

44:55.776 --> 44:58.571
-We both know what he hid there.
-A dragon's egg.

44:58.738 --> 45:00.114
MAN [WHISPERING]:
Emrys.

45:00.281 --> 45:02.074
You want the egg
to remain lost forever.

45:03.117 --> 45:06.996
This is a chance in a thousand, Merlin.

45:10.499 --> 45:11.500
No!

45:56.128 --> 45:58.130
[English - US - SDH]
